The paper deals with a unified model for vision-language pre-training, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also highly likely as the paper focuses on image captioning and visual question answering. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning and deep learning techniques. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the paper discusses pre-training and fine-tuning of models. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with information retrieval, but the techniques discussed in the paper could be applied to information retrieval tasks.
